Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.51,0:00:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,YEAR 1976
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.59,0:00:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.34,0:00:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a letter from a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.05,0:00:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a close friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.77,0:00:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 15, we tried to cross\Nthe Czechoslovakia border together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.40,0:00:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But she was captured and taken to Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.03,0:00:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She says she's doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.45,0:00:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a true friend who knows me better\Nthan even my parents or siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.29,0:00:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,With government censorship,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.16,0:00:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows what she had to do\Njust to get this letter to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.00,0:00:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She wrote, "If you have the time\Nto see me, then come meet me here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.97,0:00:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,at the sign of the Three Frogs\Nnear Cedok Bridge."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.39,0:00:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could return to Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.68,0:00:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.11,0:01:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-Say…\N-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.41,0:01:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Call me by my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.16,0:01:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for today,\NI want you to call me by my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.79,0:01:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Helenka Nováková.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.92,0:01:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for today, I'm not Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.01,0:03:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I sold my Reiserberger Pharmaceutical\Nshares at just the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.56,0:03:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I hit it big when I bought\Na little Kneuter Research stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.56,0:03:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wanted to celebrate a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.65,0:03:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,-So you had a drink?\N-Just a tiny one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.11,0:03:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.82,0:03:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only one drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.58,0:03:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to tell you?\NFor an alcoholic,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.79,0:03:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a single drink isn't any different\Nthan drinking yourself blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.04,0:03:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I see that you haven't been attending\Nthe AA group I told you about either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.59,0:03:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, doctor,\Nyou can keep a secret, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.76,0:03:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's a woman\NI'd like you to start seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.85,0:03:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have another lover?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.27,0:03:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, she's a terrible alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.40,0:03:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She's waiting outside.\NCan you speak to her for a sec?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.90,0:03:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't take drop-in patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.24,0:03:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Get an appointment for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.45,0:03:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's just for a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.24,0:04:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a house call after this\Nand they're a very important client.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.08,0:04:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to Prague in the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.12,0:04:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.21,0:04:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the fantastic Gothic cathedral\Nin Prague Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.21,0:04:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the square in the old town\Nall lit up at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.01,0:04:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a town out of a fairytale.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.30,0:04:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Cedok Bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.01,0:04:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you go to Cedok Bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.02,0:04:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. Just like you asked me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.48,0:04:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I found the Three Frogs as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.03,0:04:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the woman there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No. There was nobody there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.53,0:04:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest,\NI didn't find out anything by going there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.04,0:04:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I couldn't find Tenma,\NNina, or Dieter either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.72,0:05:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.14,0:05:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rabbit's foot. It gives good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.56,0:05:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Give that to our children\Nwhen they're born.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.90,0:05:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot… I mean, Helenka, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.70,0:05:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.71,0:05:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,PRAGUE, 1980
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.76,0:05:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,THREE FROGS
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.40,0:05:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.40,0:05:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.94,0:06:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come here from Germany\Nlooking for a woman who's gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.32,0:06:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know a woman named Margot Langer?\NI mean Helenka Nováková.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.41,0:06:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Helenka?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.46,0:06:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, Mr. Schuwald,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.59,0:06:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,your son, Karl, told me
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.59,0:06:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you haven't been eating much lately again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.34,0:06:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Your experience\Nin the fire at Munich University
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.56,0:06:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,was both horrifying and traumatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.19,0:06:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand why\Nyou're not over your fear of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.07,0:06:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But you still have…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.74,0:06:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that magnificent son of yours, Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.33,0:06:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.33,0:06:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to eat properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.58,0:06:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That monster…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.54,0:06:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as that monster exists, I just…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.55,0:07:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How did that monster know so much\Nabout Margot Langer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.51,0:07:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew far more\Nthan even me or Margot's son, Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.77,0:07:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot had a close friend in Prague\Nwho knew her better than her own family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.19,0:07:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She exchanged letters with that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.03,0:07:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Around 1980, you went in search of Margot\Nwho had gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.28,0:07:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In your search, you went to Prague\Nand met that woman, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.46,0:07:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.79,0:07:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that woman may have been\Nin contact with Margot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.75,0:07:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, she knew nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.43,0:07:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We spoke about our memories\Nof Margot for a while in her doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.14,0:07:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, they were there\Nlistening to our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.48,0:07:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.98,0:08:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They listened very carefully\Nfrom behind the woman…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.70,0:08:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,those twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.99,0:08:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.91,0:08:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.04,0:08:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Thalbach referred you to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.04,0:08:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He said you can't quit drinking either.\NAnyway, sit back and relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.75,0:08:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with a little small talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.76,0:08:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-Doctor!\N-What's wrong, Meredith?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.14,0:08:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm in the middle of a counseling--\N-He's on TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.01,0:08:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma's on TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.73,0:08:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.23,0:08:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, in top news, the suspect\Nin the poisoning deaths of three doctors
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.11,0:08:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Eisler Memorial Hospital\Nin Düsseldorf, Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.70,0:08:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the murders of the journalist,\NMaurer, and the Fortners in Heidelberg,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.24,0:08:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as the random killing\Nat Heidelberg Castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.66,0:08:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenzo Tenma, a Japanese doctor,\Nwho was hiding from police in Prague,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.75,0:09:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,was arrested on the afternoon\Nof the fifth by Czech Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.96,0:09:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We currently have no further information,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.55,0:09:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're waiting for the police to report\Non how his arrest…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.22,0:09:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.30,0:09:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't come in here.\NThis is the office area.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.97,0:09:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait in the waiting area,\NMs. Eva Heinemann!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.98,0:09:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenzo…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.77,0:09:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So sorry I'm late, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.44,0:09:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why Mr. Hesse, you look ten years younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.19,0:09:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing with my grandchildren\Nhas made me younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.82,0:09:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you doing, Hubert?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.11,0:09:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. I'm in\Nmy last year at university now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.33,0:09:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear you're pretty busy yourself,\NMr. Kiefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.04,0:09:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe I'm friends with\Na screenwriter who's going to Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.88,0:09:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help bragging about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.50,0:09:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I just happened to catch the eye\Nof a Hollywood producer. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.17,0:09:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's given me lots of ideas\Nfor all kinds of new stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.30,0:09:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.26,0:09:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to that operation…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.64,0:10:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If that brain surgery I had\Nback then hadn't succeeded,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.73,0:10:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.23,0:10:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have been able to take walks\Nwith my grandkids through the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.78,0:10:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the table…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.91,0:10:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He always sat there alone\Nenjoying his tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.83,0:10:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There were other cafes\Nwhere all the other doctors gathered,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.75,0:10:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but he would come to this little cafe\Nnear Eisler Memorial Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.25,0:10:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When we patients came in…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.01,0:10:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd look up at us from there…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And smile and wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.76,0:10:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He was such a kind doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.68,0:10:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.02,0:10:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There's absolutely no way that kind doctor\Nwould do anything like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.86,0:10:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is why I called you all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.73,0:10:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Many previous patients of Dr. Tenma
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.19,0:10:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,who couldn't come today feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.70,0:10:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Schumann, we need you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:11:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Old Mr. Merkel has collapsed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.62,0:11:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.29,0:11:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But first I've got to take care\Nof something else. Wait there a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.09,0:11:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.21,0:11:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way Dr. Tenma did such things!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.17,0:11:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down and let him talk, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.51,0:11:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to hurry up and go to him, honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.72,0:11:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know, but Petra, I can't--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.31,0:11:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you give me any "buts"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.10,0:11:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma's been arrested\Nfor crimes that he didn't commit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If it hadn't been for him,\NI wouldn't be alive anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.23,0:11:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Schumann,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.07,0:11:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,are you saying you won't help\Nthe man who saved your wife's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.41,0:11:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-What will happen to this village?\N-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.20,0:11:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the only doctor in this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.25,0:11:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If I leave,\Nwhat will everyone in this town do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.50,0:11:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough of your grumbling!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.34,0:11:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you want to go!\NSo get going and help Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.55,0:11:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A doctor cannot leave his patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma would do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, hurry up and see us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.39,0:12:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Be patient! I'm still getting ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.65,0:12:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,-How long do we have to wait?\N-Quit complaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.77,0:12:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor's been studying\Nat a proper med school lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.61,0:12:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as running this place,\Neven though she ain't licensed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.57,0:12:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you are in the darkness,\Nyou just sink deeper into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your light shining.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.67,0:12:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can become a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.04,0:12:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll make a fine doctor for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.05,0:12:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.31,0:12:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll start seeing you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.52,0:12:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever's first, get in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.06,0:12:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-Get my lawyer.\N-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.61,0:12:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But we still don't know where Tenma\Nwill be sent to in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.07,0:13:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me a lawyer from every state.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.03,0:13:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Find the best criminal lawyers out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.12,0:13:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yes, sir.\N-He's the only man…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the feeling\Nhe's the only man who can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.42,0:13:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the only one\Nwho can eliminate that monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.88,0:13:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We need as many allies as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.89,0:13:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's contact all\Nof Dr. Tenma's former patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.47,0:13:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we can't do much individually,\Nby working together, we can do a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.94,0:13:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got an idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.65,0:13:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get Eisler Memorial Hospital\Nto help us set up a relief society!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.57,0:13:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll never work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.86,0:13:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way Eisler Memorial Hospital\Nwill ever agree to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.62,0:13:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been listening to you.\NWhat you've said has been very touching.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But think about it realistically.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.42,0:13:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you possibly prove\NTenma's innocence?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.26,0:14:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Becker…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.43,0:14:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he's got plenty of motive,\Nbut he's got no alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.10,0:14:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They said they've got\Nactual physical evidence, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.35,0:14:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, you can get a bunch\Nof people together and make a fuss,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.73,0:14:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but no matter how competent\Nthe lawyer you hire is,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll still be impossible\Nto prove Tenma's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.62,0:14:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pity though.\NHe was such a gifted doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.91,0:14:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.29,0:14:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.38,0:14:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just exactly what is\Nyour connection with Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.05,0:14:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann, I don't know who you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.60,0:14:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm going to help Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:14:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you tagging along\Nif you're just here for your enjoyment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.90,0:14:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.90,0:15:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Heinemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.65,0:15:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Don't tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.66,0:15:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the daughter of Director Heinemann\Nwho was murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.04,0:15:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,at Eisler Memorial Hospital in Düsseldorf.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.20,0:15:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.91,0:15:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the man who destroyed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.29,0:15:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know what?\NI'm the only one who can save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.01,0:15:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Saw what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.98,0:15:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A decision has been made\Nto extradite Kenzo Tenma
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.06,0:15:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to Germany in the next day or two\Nfrom where he was arrested in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.19,0:15:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's presumed that he'll be sent\Nto Düsseldorf where his crimes began.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.91,0:15:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,After he's questioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.03,0:15:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible. That's just not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.37,0:15:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This man…\NThis doctor couldn't do those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.21,0:15:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.79,0:16:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Suk, you owe him your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.17,0:16:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the doctor who gave you first aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.05,0:16:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma's also been\Naccused of crimes he never committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.05,0:16:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in the same situation as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.10,0:16:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe him my life,\Nbut he's in the same situation as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.23,0:16:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a detective, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.65,0:16:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As a detective, you must calmly dissect\Nand investigate everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.99,0:16:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to be betrayed anymore…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.91,0:16:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then suspect the person\Nyou least want to suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.83,0:16:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.54,0:16:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to get to Prague Police Station\Nand speak with Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.76,0:16:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been looking for you, Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.26,0:16:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective Blazek.\NDetective Stransky. I didn't--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.81,0:17:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to run anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.15,0:17:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been through a heck of a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.78,0:17:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But you've been cleared now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.03,0:17:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We received a letter at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.45,0:17:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a copy of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.82,0:17:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.74,0:17:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a confession containing details
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.91,0:17:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the crimes\Nonly the murderer could know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.50,0:17:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been cleared of all suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.79,0:17:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wrote that letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.50,0:17:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A guy named Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.92,0:17:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.34,0:17:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been placed\Non the most wanted list as a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.47,0:17:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.47,0:17:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry anymore, Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.02,0:17:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This clears up all the cases,\Nthe beating death of Inspector Zeman,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.56,0:17:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the poisoning of the commissioner,\Nand the shooting
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the two task force members.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.13,0:18:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the heck have you been, Lunge?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.09,0:18:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've called you several times!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.18,0:19:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Chief.\NI was doing some sightseeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.97,0:19:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your problem?\NDon't play dumb with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.69,0:19:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Play dumb"? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.56,0:19:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough of this!\NDon't tell me you haven't seen the news!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.28,0:19:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,JAPANESE DOCTOR CAPTURED IN PRAGUE
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.99,0:19:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean about the arrest of Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.03,0:19:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.16,0:19:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.24,0:19:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew Tenma was hiding in Prague,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.54,0:19:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, Lunge. Your persistence in\Nthis investigation has paid off at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.29,0:19:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Our people here at BKA have contacted\Nthe Czech Police and arranged things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.05,0:19:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma will be transported\Nto Düsseldorf tomorrow afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.72,0:19:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you're in charge of this case,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.85,0:19:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to handle\Nhis transfer personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I've really got to hand it to you, Lunge.\NCongratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.06,0:19:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Send someone else to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.44,0:19:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.44,0:19:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Prague is a beautiful city.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.40,0:19:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.40,0:19:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I'm on vacation right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.11,0:20:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lunge!\NWhat the heck's gotten into you? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.20,0:20:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me speak with Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.83,0:20:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already told you!\NYou can't speak with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.71,0:20:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then tell me why!\NI thought this was a democratic country!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.21,0:20:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma's going to be extradited to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.09,0:20:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let me see him\Nfor a moment before then!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.47,0:20:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like this was a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.93,0:20:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,After all the effort we spent\Ngetting to Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.56,0:20:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm begging you! Just a brief minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.10,0:20:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.48,0:20:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.87,0:20:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When we interrogate people,\Nwho do you think
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.21,0:20:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is the hardest to deal with?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.00,0:20:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The people whose expression\Nnever changes no matter what we say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.13,0:20:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who don't say a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.47,0:21:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the hardest kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.90,0:21:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Monster's Love Letter to the Beauty."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.40,0:21:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a draft of a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.32,0:21:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,"I've always watched you."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.12,0:21:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"I've watched you\Nso I could devour all of you."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.41,0:21:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"But everything about you has\Ndevoured me instead."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.58,0:21:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"As I was falling to pieces,\Nhow did I appear to you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.55,0:21:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"As I fell to pieces,\Nyou gave me something."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.14,0:21:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"You left me with beautiful gems,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.76,0:21:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,those twins who seem to have eternal\Nlife."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.44,0:21:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"The greatest crime is\Nto steal someone's name."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.82,0:21:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's get your name back."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.98,0:21:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'll give you your name back."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.07,0:22:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"Your name is Anna."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.74,0:22:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"Now, I am simply sad."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.33,0:22:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sad…"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.66,0:22:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sad…"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.00,0:22:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sad…"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.79,0:22:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.63,0:22:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people died in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.42,0:22:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, a horrific monster was born.
